modules.description: Provides functions for efficient manipulation of Bigstring data, including direct memory operations and conversions between Bigstrings and standard strings. Works with Bigstring.t and string types, enabling low-level buffer management. Enables high-performance data processing in network protocols and file I/O where speed and memory control are critical.

This module offers low-level byte manipulation, including integer serialization/deserialization (int16, int32, int64) in both endiannesses, raw memory copying, and direct access to binary data, optimized for performance. It works with Bigarray-based bigstrings, enabling efficient memory-sharing via views and direct interaction with string-like types. Use cases include high-performance networking, binary file parsing, or systems where minimal overhead in data transformation is critical.
